gene bridge_uplink
  is configuration
  risk low

  does:
    Attach an uplink interface to an existing bridge. The uplink is the
    interface that connects the bridge to the upstream network â€” typically
    a physical NIC or a bond.

  takes:
    bridge_name  string  "Bridge to attach the uplink to"
    uplink       string  "Interface to use as uplink"

  gives:
    success  bool    "Whether the uplink was attached"
    error    string? "Error message on failure"

  before:
    - Bridge exists
    - Uplink interface exists and is not already enslaved

  after:
    - Uplink interface is attached as a bridge port
    - Bridge has connectivity to upstream network

  fails when:
    - bridge does not exist -> success=false
    - uplink interface not found -> success=false
    - uplink already enslaved -> success=false
